<item>
            <title>[CXF-5161] AbstranctGrantHandler checks against &quot;authorization_code&quot; instead of supplied grant type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5161</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the given commit the method checkIfGrantSupported was changed. This breaks my application. Is this by design or is it a bug? It worked in Version 2.7.5&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/cxf/trunk/rt/rs/security/oauth-parent/oauth2/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/rs/security/oauth2/grants/AbstractGrantHandler.java?r1=1491522&amp;amp;r2=1489392&amp;amp;diff_format=h&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/cxf/trunk/rt/rs/security/oauth-parent/oauth2/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/rs/security/oauth2/grants/AbstractGrantHandler.java?r1=1491522&amp;amp;r2=1489392&amp;amp;diff_format=h&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
